# Paperclip Setup Walkthrough

I have successfully cloned the Paperclip repository, installed all dependencies, and created a startup script to get you running quickly.

## Changes Made

### 1. Repository Setup
- **Cloned**: `https://github.com/paperclipai/paperclip` into [paperclip](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip).
- **Dependencies**: Ran `pnpm install` across the entire workspace.
- **Database Reset**: Fixed a PostgreSQL initialization issue on Windows by resetting the embedded database directory.

### 2. Startup Automation
- **New File**: Created [run.bat](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/run.bat) in the root directory.
- **Functionality**:
    - Starts the dev server in the background using `pnpm dev`.
    - Polls the `/api/health` endpoint until the server is ready.
    - Automatically opens `http://localhost:3100` in your default browser.

## Getting Started

To launch the project, simply double-click the `run.bat` file in the root directory or run it from your terminal:

```powershell
./run.bat
```

> [!NOTE]
> The first time you run the project, it will automatically apply migrations to your local embedded database. This process is handled by the `pnpm dev` command.

> [!TIP]
> If you encounter any database errors in the future, you can reset the local database by deleting the `C:\Users\Admin\.paperclip\instances\default\db` folder.

